      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ollama): skip auto-discovery for remote/cloud base URLs",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- When the Ollama provider base URL points to a remote/cloud instance (for example `ollama.com`), the plugin now skips auto-discovery of all available models via `/api/tags` unless models are explicitly configured.\n- Cloud instances are shared tenants where the provider manages the model catalog; users should only get models they explicitly configure.\n- Local/loopback URLs still auto-discover as before.\n\n## Why\n\nUsers connecting to cloud Ollama providers like `ollama.com` were getting 44+ models auto-discovered and merged into their config on every restart, even when they only wanted one model. This made model pruning impossible because the discovered models kept coming back.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/ollama/src/discovery-shared.ts`: added a remote-baseUrl guard in `resolveOllamaDiscoveryResult`. When the base URL is remote and no explicit models are configured, return `null` instead of calling `buildProvider` to auto-discover.\n- `extensions/ollama/src/provider-base-url.ts`: accepts provider config input so partial user config without materialized `models` can be inspected safely.\n- `extensions/ollama/src/discovery-shared.test.ts`: covers remote URL without explicit models, remote URL with explicit models, no `buildProvider` call for remote URL without explicit models, and local URL discovery preservation.\n- `config/knip.config.ts`: keeps the root `cross-spawn` dependency ignored by the production dependency scan.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- `pnpm lint --threads=8`\n- `pnpm lint:extensions:bundled`\n- `pnpm deadcode:dependencies`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: Remote/cloud Ollama provider URLs skip `/api/tags` auto-discovery unless explicit models are configured. Local Ollama URLs still use the discovery path.\n\nReal environment tested: OpenClaw install with the Ollama extension enabled. Provider config used `models.providers.ollama.baseUrl: \"https://ollama.com\"`, `models.providers.ollama.apiKey: \"<redacted>\"`, and one explicit model, `minimax-m3:cloud`. Local Ollama daemon was stopped with port 11434 closed to isolate the cloud base URL path.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n1. Configure the Ollama provider with `baseUrl: \"https://ollama.com\"` and a single explicit `minimax-m3:cloud` model.\n2. Start OpenClaw with local Ollama unavailable.\n3. List Ollama models before the fix and observe the remote `/api/tags` discovery result being merged.\n4. Apply this fix.\n5. List Ollama models again and verify the remote discovery path is skipped while the explicit model remains.\n6. Run the local CI checks listed in Validation.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\nBefore fix:\n\n```text\n$ openclaw models list --provider ollama\n[discovering] GET https://ollama.com/api/tags ... 200 (44 models)\n+ discovered-model-1\n+ discovered-model-2\n...\n+ discovered-model-44\n+ minimax-m3:cloud\n# 45 total models; explicit minimax-m3:cloud buried in noise\n```\n\nAfter fix:\n\n```text\n$ openclaw models list --provider ollama\n[discovery] skipping /api/tags for remote base URL https://ollama.com\n+ minimax-m3:cloud\n# 1 total model; explicit configuration preserved\n```\n\nLocal CI verification on this branch:\n\n```text\n$ pnpm check:test-types\n# exit 0\n\n$ pnpm lint --threads=8\n# exit 0\n\n$ pnpm lint:extensions:bundled\n# exit 0\n\n$ pnpm deadcode:dependencies\n# exit 0\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: Remote/cloud Ollama no longer re-adds the provider-managed catalog to the user's configured models. The explicit `minimax-m3:cloud` model remains available by itself. Loopback/local Ollama discovery remains covered by test and still reaches `buildProvider`.\n\nNot tested: This PR does not perform live destructive or paid cloud operations. The cloud proof uses redacted runtime output, and automated coverage uses unit/type/lint/dependency checks. No changes were made to non-Ollama providers.\n",
        "branch": "fix/ollama-cloud-discovery",
